#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid "Making the most of &kmymoney;"
msgstr "Kar najbolje izkoristiti &kmymoney;"

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid "Help improve this Handbook"
msgstr "Pomagajte izboljšati ta priročnik"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:16
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This and the following sections have had no significant updates since the "
"very early versions of &kmymoney;. While the basics of bookkeeping have not "
"changed over the years, and there is nothing inaccurate or misleading here, "
"there have been requests to update this area. If you have any specific "
"suggestions or ideas for this, the author would like to hear from you, "
"through one of the routes listed at the <ulink url=\"https://kmymoney.org/"
"support.html\">Support page</ulink> at the <ulink url=\"https://kmymoney.org/"
"\">&kmymoney; web site</ulink>"
msgstr ""
"Ta in naslednji razdelki niso imeli večjih posodobitev od zelo zgodnjih "
"različic &kmymoney;. Čeprav se osnove knjigovodstva skozi leta niso "
"spremenile in tu ni nič netočnega ali zavajajočega, so bile zahteve po "
"posodobitvi tega področja. Če imate kakršne koli posebne predloge ali ideje "
"za to, vas avtor želi slišati po eni od poti, navedenih na <ulink url="
"\"https://kmymoney.org/support.html\">strani za podporo</ulink> na <ulink "
"url=\"https://kmymoney.org/\"> spletnem mestu &kmymoney;</ulink>"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:27
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While much of &kmymoney; might be obvious to a naive user, and you could go "
"ahead, clicking some buttons and filling in some data, after a time, you "
"might decide you have done it wrong and want to start again, even if you did "
"read the documentation on each part of &kmymoney;."
msgstr ""
"Čeprav je velik del &kmymoney; lahko naivnemu uporabniku očiten in lahko "
"nadaljujete, kliknete nekaj gumbov in vnesete nekaj podatkov, po določenem "
"času pa se lahko odločite, da ste kaj naredili narobe in želite začeti "
"znova, tudi če ste prebrali dokumentacijo o vsakem delu  &kmymoney;."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:34
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You will get a more efficient and effective system and much better use of "
"your time if you first spend a little time planning how you are going to use "
"&kmymoney;, so follow the steps given here. This may seem very simple, and "
"indeed, it is simple, but taking the time to assure that your understanding "
"of how things work is the same as &kmymoney;'s will almost certainly save "
"you time later."
msgstr ""
"Dobili boste učinkovitejši in uspešnejši sistem ter veliko boljšo porabo "
"svojega časa, če boste najprej porabili nekaj časa za načrtovanje, kako "
"boste uporabljali &kmymoney;, zato sledite tukaj podanim korakom. To se "
"morda zdi zelo preprosto in res je preprosto, toda če si vzamete čas in "
"zagotovite, da je vaše razumevanje delovanja stvari enako kot &kmymoney;, "
"vam bo kasneje skoraj zagotovo prihranilo čas."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:42
#, no-c-format
msgid "Basic Accounting"
msgstr "Osnovno računovodstvo"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Imagine your money as balls, or beans, and to stop them rolling around and "
"getting lost you keep them in a box, or pot. Accounting, or Bookkeeping, is "
"the process of counting and keeping track of the beans in the pot, or more "
"important, the beans in several pots."
msgstr ""
"Predstavljajte si svoj denar kot kroglice ali zrna in da se preprečijo "
"kotalijo in izgubijo, jih hranite v škatli ali loncu. Računovodstvo ali "
"knjigovodstvo je postopek štetja in spremljanja fižola v loncu ali še "
"pomembneje, fižola v več loncih."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You have some money in the pot marked <quote>Cash</quote>. You buy some "
"goods, so you take some beans out of the cash pot and place them into "
"another pot marked <quote>Supplier</quote>. The supplier gives you some "
"goods in exchange for the cash, so you take the beans out of the pot marked "
"<quote>Supplier</quote> and put them in the pot marked <quote>Goods</quote>."
msgstr ""
"V lončku z oznako <quote>Denar</quote> imate nekaj denarja. Kupite nekaj "
"blaga, zato iz lončka za denar vzamete nekaj fižola in ga položite v drug "
"lonček z oznako <quote>Dobavitelj</quote>. Dobavitelj vam da nekaj blaga v "
"zameno za denar, tako da fižol vzamete iz lončka z oznako <quote>Dobavitelj</"
"quote> in ga daste v lonček z oznako <quote>Blago</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goods have a value (the price you paid) so you still have the same "
"amount of beans, some representing cash and some representing goods."
msgstr ""
"Blago ima vrednost (ceno, ki ste jo plačali), tako da imate še vedno enako "
"količino fižola, nekaj predstavlja gotovino, nekaj pa blago."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:63
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this case you have two movements of beans, or transactions. Each "
"transaction needs two entries, one to take beans out and one to put beans "
"in. This is called <quote>double entry bookkeeping</quote> or <quote>double "
"entry accounting</quote>. The recording of the transactions is done in a "
"<quote>Ledger</quote>; each pot is known as an <quote>Account</quote> or "
"<quote>Ledger code</quote>."
msgstr ""
"V tem primeru imate dva premika fižola ali transakcije. Vsaka transakcija "
"potrebuje dva vnosa, enega za odvzem fižola in enega za vlaganje fižola. To "
"se imenuje <quote>dvostavno knjigovodstvo</quote> ali <quote>dvostavno "
"računovodstvo</quote>. Evidentiranje transakcij poteka v <quote>Glavni "
"knjigi</quote>; vsak lonček je znan kot <quote>Račun</quote> ali <quote>Koda "
"knjiženja</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you take some goods and give them to a customer, who gives you some cash "
"in exchange. The goods were worth some beans and, hopefully, the customer "
"has given us more beans than that, so making a profit. To over simplify, the "
"beans from the Goods pot come back as Cash, but we can split that as the "
"<quote>Cost of Goods sold</quote> and <quote>Profit</quote>. This "
"transaction has three entries; one side of the <quote>double entry</quote> "
"has been split."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj vzamete nekaj blaga in ga daste stranki, ki vam v zameno da nekaj "
"gotovine. Blago je bilo vredno nekaj fižola in upajmo, da nam je kupec dal "
"več fižola od tega, tako da ustvarja dobiček. Če preveč poenostavimo, se "
"fižol iz lonca blaga vrne kot denar, vendar ga lahko razdelimo kot "
"<quote>stroške prodanega blaga</quote> in <quote>dobiček</quote>. Ta "
"transakcija ima tri vnose; ena stran <quote>dvojnega vnosa</quote> je bila "
"razdeljena."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This will be covered in more detail later on in this handbook in the section "
"on <link linkend=\"details.ledgers.split\">split transactions</link>."
msgstr ""
"To bo podrobneje obravnavano pozneje v tem priročniku v razdelku o <link "
"linkend=\"details.ledgers.split\">razcepljenih transakcijah</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defining the accounts (personal records)"
msgstr "Definiranje računov (osebnih evidenc)"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most accounts, or pots, as described above, represent a measure of our "
"<quote>Worth</quote>. The cash and goods represent our <quote>Assets</"
"quote>, which also include any amount someone owes us for goods we provided "
"or money we loaned to them. The money we owe to others, say if we had not "
"paid our suppliers, are our <quote>Liabilities</quote>. These accounts are "
"transferable to Cash and have a value."
msgstr ""
"Večina računov ali loncev, kot je opisano zgoraj, predstavlja merilo naše "
"<quote>vrednosti</quote>. Gotovina in blago predstavljata naše "
"<quote>Premoženje</quote>, ki vključuje tudi vse zneske, ki nam jih nekdo "
"dolguje za blago, ki smo mu ga zagotovili, ali denar, ki smo mu ga posodili. "
"Denar, ki ga dolgujemo drugim, na primer, če ne bi plačali svojim "
"dobaviteljem, so naše <quote>Obveznosti</quote>. Ti računi so prenosljivi v "
"gotovino in imajo vrednost."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any pots that cannot be valued are <quote>Income</quote> or <quote>Expense</"
"quote>. Our phone bill (or the phone company to which we pay the bill) "
"cannot be valued; we know how much we have paid, but not how much anyone "
"else has paid. We know how much our employer has paid us, but we do not know "
"how much they have paid anybody else, or how much money they have left to "
"pay us next month. Although we cannot determine an actual value for these "
"pots, it is useful to monitor how much we have put into or taken out of each "
"of them."
msgstr ""
"Vsi lončki, ki jih ni mogoče ovrednotiti, so <quote>Dohodki</quote> ali "
"<quote>Stroški</quote>. Našega telefonskega računa (ali telefonskega "
"podjetja, ki mu plačamo račun) ni mogoče ovrednotiti; vemo, koliko smo "
"plačali mi, ne pa tudi, koliko je plačal kdo drug. Vemo, koliko nam je "
"delodajalec plačal, ne vemo pa, koliko je plačal komu drugemu, ali koliko "
"denarja nam je ostalo, da nam ga plača naslednji mesec. Čeprav za te lončke "
"ne moremo določiti dejanske vrednosti, je koristno spremljati, koliko smo "
"dali v vsakega od njih ali iz njega vzeli."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In some cases a supplier is a <quote>Liability,</quote> in others it is an "
"<quote>Expense</quote>. This is something we need to consider and decide for "
"each case. Similarly, you may set up a loan as a Liability, particularly if "
"you transfer the money into your bank account, but it could be an Expense if "
"it was to buy some furniture."
msgstr ""
"V nekaterih primerih je dobavitelj <quote>Obveznost</quote>, v drugih pa "
"<quote>Strošek</quote>. To je nekaj, kar moramo upoštevati in se odločiti za "
"vsak primer posebej. Podobno lahko nastavite posojilo kot obveznost, zlasti "
"če denar nakažete na svoj bančni račun, vendar bi lahko bil strošek, če bi "
"šlo za nakup pohištva."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Consider how you want to track and analyze your income and expenses. This "
"will help you decide how to set them up in &kmymoney;."
msgstr ""
"Razmislite, kako želite slediti in analizirati svoje prihodke in odhodke. To "
"vam bo pomagalo pri odločitvi, kako jih nastaviti v &kmymoney;."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Finally, consider if you want everything in one set of accounts, or two or "
"more. This may depend on the legal framework where you live, or just how you "
"want to analyze things. Each set of accounts would be handled separately."
msgstr ""
"Na koncu razmislite, ali želite vse v enem nizu računov ali dveh ali več. To "
"je lahko odvisno od pravnega okvira, v katerem živite, ali od tega, kako "
"želite analizirati stvari. Vsak niz računov bi se obravnaval ločeno."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defining the accounts (business records)"
msgstr "Definiranje računov (poslovne evidence)"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are similarities to setting up accounts for personal use, but there "
"are additional considerations, including legal guidelines and requirements. "
"&kmymoney; does not explicitly address any of these issues, as it has been "
"designed as a <quote>personal</quote> finance manager. In addition, these "
"additional issues are not addressed in this handbook, but you must be aware "
"of them if you are going to attempt to use &kmymoney; for a business."
msgstr ""
"Obstajajo podobnosti z nastavitvijo računov za osebno uporabo, vendar "
"obstajajo dodatni vidiki, vključno s pravnimi smernicami in zahtevami. "
"&kmymoney; ne obravnava izrecno nobene od teh težav, saj je bil zasnovan kot "
"<quote>osebni</quote> upravljalnik financ. Poleg tega ta dodatna vprašanja "
"niso obravnavana v tem priročniku, vendar se jih morate zavedati, če boste "
"poskušali uporabiti &kmymoney; za podjetje."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mapping your finances to &kmymoney;"
msgstr "Preslikava vaših financ v &kmymoney;"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"So, collect your recent financial papers and explore the following sections "
"for more information on how you can map your own finances to each of the "
"different areas of &kmymoney;. Note that each of these sections below is "
"presented in more detail in later chapters of this handbook."
msgstr ""
"Torej, zberite svoje nedavne finančne dokumente in raziščite naslednje "
"razdelke za več informacij o tem, kako lahko svoje finance preslikate na "
"vsako od različnih področij &kmymoney;. Upoštevajte, da je vsak od teh "
"spodnjih razdelkov podrobneje predstavljen v naslednjih poglavjih tega "
"priročnika."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:148
#, no-c-format
msgid "Accounts"
msgstr "Računi"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An <quote>Account</quote> in &kmymoney; represents one of the <quote>pots</"
"quote> of the previous section: it can be anywhere which holds your money "
"and possessions that you wish to monitor. You generally create an account in "
"&kmymoney; to represent each different account you have in <quote>real life,"
"</quote> whether it is with a bank or other financial institution, or a "
"store, or even just the cash in your wallet. There are several types of "
"accounts available, which represent different types of places your money may "
"be."
msgstr ""
"<quote>Račun</quote> v &kmymoney; predstavlja enega od <quote>skladišč</"
"quote> prejšnjega razdelka: lahko je kjer koli, kjer je vaš denar in imetje, "
"ki ga želite nadzorovati. Običajno ustvarite račun v &kmymoney; za "
"predstavljanje vsakega drugega računa, ki ga imate v <quote>resničnem "
"življenju</quote>, ne glede na to, ali gre za banko ali drugo finančno "
"institucijo, trgovino ali celo samo gotovino v vaši denarnici. Na voljo je "
"več vrst računov, ki predstavljajo različne vrste mest, kjer je lahko vaš "
"denar."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:159
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Transactions (to be described in more detail later) are created to indicate "
"money moving in or out of one or more accounts."
msgstr ""
"Transakcije (podrobneje bodo opisane kasneje) so ustvarjene za prikaz "
"denarja, ki se premika v ali iz enega ali več računov."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As described below, accounts can either hold money which is actually yours "
"(assets) or money which you owe (liabilities.) Liabilities can be thought of "
"as magic pots, which you can take beans from even if there are not actually "
"any beans there, but which you eventually need to replace."
msgstr ""
"Kot je opisano spodaj, lahko računi hranijo denar, ki je dejansko vaš "
"(imetje) ali denar, ki ga dolgujete (obveznosti). ki pa ga boste sčasoma "
"morali zamenjati."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "Accounts - Asset"
msgstr "Računi – Imetje"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are multiple types of Asset Accounts. They are all essentially the "
"same, in holding your money, but there are some differences in the details "
"of how money enters and leaves the different types of accounts."
msgstr ""
"Obstaja več vrst računov imetja. Vsi so v bistvu enaki glede hrambe vašega "
"denarja, vendar obstajajo nekatere razlike v podrobnostih, kako denar vstopi "
"in zapusti različne vrste računov."

#. Tag: term
#: makemostof.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid "Checking"
msgstr "Čeki"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:183
#, no-c-format
msgid "Standard bank checking account."
msgstr "Standardni bančni tekoči račun."

#. Tag: term
#: makemostof.docbook:190
#, no-c-format
msgid "Savings"
msgstr "Varčevanje"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:192
#, no-c-format
msgid "Standard bank savings account."
msgstr "Standardni bančni varčevalni račun."

#. Tag: term
#: makemostof.docbook:199
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cash"
msgstr "Gotovina"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:201
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Money in your pocket or your wallet or in a jar or box on the shelf or under "
"your bed."
msgstr ""
"Denar v žepu ali denarnici ali v kozarcu ali škatli na polici ali pod "
"posteljo."

#. Tag: term
#: makemostof.docbook:209 makemostof.docbook:253
#, no-c-format
msgid "Loan"
msgstr "Posojilo"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:211
#, no-c-format
msgid "Loans you make to someone else."
msgstr "Posojila, ki jih daste nekomu drugemu."

#. Tag: term
#: makemostof.docbook:218
#, no-c-format
msgid "Investment"
msgstr "Naložba"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "Money you invest."
msgstr "Denar, ki ga investirate."

#. Tag: term
#: makemostof.docbook:227
#, no-c-format
msgid "Asset"
msgstr "Imetje"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid "Property, collections, &etc;"
msgstr "Lastnina, zbirke, &etc;"

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Accounts - Liability"
msgstr "Računi - Obveznost"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:238
#, no-c-format
msgid "These accounts represent your debts and money you owe to others."
msgstr "Ti računi predstavljajo vaše dolgove in denar, ki ga dolgujete drugim."

#. Tag: term
#: makemostof.docbook:244
#, no-c-format
msgid "Credit card"
msgstr "Kreditna kartica"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid "Standard credit card account."
msgstr "Standardni račun kreditne kartice."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid "Loans made to you, mortgages, &etc;"
msgstr "Posojila za vas, hipoteke, &etc;"

#. Tag: term
#: makemostof.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid "Liability"
msgstr "Obveznost"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Anything else you owe that does not fit the other liability account types."
msgstr ""
"Karkoli drugega, kar dolgujete, kar ne ustreza drugim vrstam računov "
"obveznosti."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:273
#, no-c-format
msgid "Institutions"
msgstr "Institucije"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These represent financial institutions, such as banks or stores or "
"investment brokers. They can be used to group accounts, and can show the "
"total value of all your accounts within that institution. These do not need "
"to reflect actual organizations, but are for your convenience in grouping "
"your accounts. Their use is completely optional."
msgstr ""
"Ti predstavljajo finančne institucije, kot so banke ali trgovine ali "
"investicijski posredniki. Uporabljajo se lahko za združevanje računov in "
"lahko prikažejo skupno vrednost vseh vaših računov v tej instituciji. Ni "
"nujno, da odražajo dejanske organizacije, ampak so za vaše udobje pri "
"združevanju vaših računov. Njihova uporaba je popolnoma neobvezna."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:283
#, no-c-format
msgid "Categories"
msgstr "Kategorije"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:284
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A Category is a special type of account used internally by &kmymoney; to "
"track income and expenses. These accounts are non-managed, because as "
"mentioned earlier, they do not have real values, and show only what you have "
"gotten from them or contributed to them. Each category shows the total value "
"of transactions which mention it. The principle of double entry accounting "
"requires that every transaction includes a category or transfer account. "
"This will also be explained in more detail later in the handbook."
msgstr ""
"Kategorija je posebna vrsta računa, ki ga interno uporablja &kmymoney; za "
"spremljanje prihodkov in odhodkov. Ti računi so neupravljani, ker, kot je "
"bilo že omenjeno, nimajo prave vrednosti in prikazujejo samo tisto, kar ste "
"od njih dobili ali prispevali vanje. Vsaka kategorija prikazuje skupno "
"vrednost transakcij, ki jo omenjajo. Načelo dvostavnega računovodstva "
"zahteva, da vsaka transakcija vključuje kategorijo ali prenosni račun. Tudi "
"to bo podrobneje pojasnjeno kasneje v priročniku."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Income Categories are used as places from which you receive money, and "
"Expense Categories represent purposes for which you spend money. On rare "
"occasion, money can flow the \"wrong\" way, such as getting a refund for an "
"over-payment of a utility bill."
msgstr ""
"Kategorije dohodka se uporabljajo kot mesta, od koder prejemate denar, "
"kategorije stroškov pa predstavljajo namene, za katere porabite denar. V "
"redkih primerih lahko denar teče v \"napačno\" smer, kot je na primer "
"vračilo preplačanega računa za komunalne storitve."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sub-Categories"
msgstr "Pod-kategorije"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:302
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Categories can be split into sub-categories, but this relationship is "
"primarily for your convenience, and is used for display purposes. Most of "
"the time, the sub-category totals are not included in the higher level "
"category total, although there are specific reports and displays where this "
"can be done."
msgstr ""
"Kategorije je mogoče razdeliti na podkategorije, vendar je to razmerje "
"namenjeno predvsem vašemu udobju in se uporablja za namene prikaza. Večino "
"časa vsote podkategorije niso vključene v vsoto kategorije višje ravni, "
"čeprav obstajajo posebna poročila in prikazi, kjer je to mogoče storiti."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:312
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tags"
msgstr "Oznake"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Tags are very similar to Categories, as they are also non-managed accounts "
"that do not have a value. However, unlike Categories, the use of Tags is "
"completely optional. They can be used to group transactions for reporting "
"purposes."
msgstr ""
"Značke so zelo podobne kategorijam, saj so prav tako neupravljani računi, ki "
"nimajo vrednosti. Vendar pa je za razliko od kategorij uporaba značk "
"popolnoma neobvezna. Uporabljajo se lahko za združevanje transakcij za "
"namene poročanja."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:320
#, no-c-format
msgid "Payees"
msgstr "Prejemniki plačil"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:321
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A Payee (or Payer) represents someone or some group to which you pay money "
"or which pays you money. As with Tags, they are non-managed, and do not have "
"a value. They are primarily a convenience for being able to report how much "
"money you have sent to someone or spent at a particular store. These are "
"optional for most transactions, but are required for Scheduled transactions, "
"which are describe below. A transaction history, with categories, can be "
"shown for each payee."
msgstr ""
"Prejemnik plačila (ali plačnik) predstavlja nekoga ali neko skupino, ki ji "
"plačate denar ali ki vam plača denar. Tako kot pri značkah tudi te niso "
"upravljane in nimajo vrednosti. So predvsem udobje, saj lahko poročate, "
"koliko denarja ste nekomu poslali ali porabili v določeni trgovini. Te so "
"neobvezne za večino transakcij, vendar so obvezne za načrtovane transakcije, "
"ki so opisane spodaj. Za vsakega prejemnika plačila je mogoče prikazati "
"zgodovino transakcij s kategorijami."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:331
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scheduled transactions"
msgstr "Načrtovane transakcije"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Where transactions occur on a regular basis, such as salary or utility "
"bills, these can be set up against a Schedule. Transactions are created from "
"Schedules. Upcoming scheduled transaction as well as those which are overdue "
"can be shown on the home page."
msgstr ""
"Če se transakcije izvajajo redno, kot so plače ali računi za komunalne "
"storitve, jih je mogoče nastaviti glede na plan plačil. Transakcije se "
"ustvarijo iz plana plačil. Prihajajoče načrtovane transakcije in tiste, ki "
"so zapadle, so lahko prikazane na domači strani."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:341
#, no-c-format
msgid "Useful Tips"
msgstr "Koristni nasveti"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:342
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you start &kmymoney;, the Home View, or Home Page, shows a high level "
"overview of your finances. It is divided into several sections, and you can "
"customize which are displayed, and in what order. Along the left, there are "
"icons for each of the major Views. Each view is used by &kmymoney; to "
"present a different type of data for entry or review."
msgstr ""
"Ko zaženete &kmymoney;, pogled domače strani ali domača stran prikaže visoko "
"raven pregleda vaših financ. Razdeljen je na več razdelkov in lahko "
"prilagodite, kateri so prikazani in v kakšnem vrstnem redu. Na levi strani "
"so ikone za vsakega od glavnih pogledov. Vsak pogled uporablja &kmymoney; za "
"predstavitev drugačne vrste podatkov za vnos ali pregled."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:350
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Unless you keep your money under your mattress or under the floorboards, you "
"probably make use of one or more institutions, where you have accounts, "
"which may be in credit or debit. In order to familiarize yourself with the "
"way &kmymoney; works, choose an account you want to track with &kmymoney; "
"and select the <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>New</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice> menu item in order to set up a data file."
msgstr ""
"Če denarja ne hranite pod žimnico ali pod talnimi deskami, verjetno "
"uporabljate eno ali več institucij, kjer imate račune, ki so lahko kreditni "
"ali debetni. Da bi se seznanili z načinom kako &kmymoney; deluje, izberite "
"račun, ki mu želite slediti z &kmymoney; in izberite menijsko postavko "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Novo</guimenuitem> </"
"menuchoice>, da nastavite podatkovno datoteko."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:359
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have used another personal finance manager, you may be able to import "
"the data from it into &kmymoney;."
msgstr ""
"Če ste že uporabljali drugega upravljalnika osebnih financ, boste morda "
"lahko podatke iz njega uvozili v &kmymoney;."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have some regular receipts into or outgoings from this account, you "
"can go to the Payees View and enter the names of both the payers and the "
"payees involved; then go to Scheduled Transactions View and fill in a New "
"Schedule for each recurring transaction. If you haven't entered the payee or "
"payer, &kmymoney; will offer you the opportunity to do this in the middle of "
"entering the Schedule."
msgstr ""
"Če imate redne prejemke na ta račun ali odhodke iz tega računa, lahko "
"odprete pogled prejemnikov in vnesete imena vpletenih plačnikov in "
"prejemnikov plačil; nato pojdite na Pogled načrtovanih transakcij in "
"izpolnite Nov časovni plan za vsako ponavljajočo se transakcijo. Če niste "
"vnesli prejemnika plačila ali plačnika, vam bo &kmymoney; ponudil možnost, "
"da to storite sredi vnosa v časovni plan."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:372
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add other transactions go to the Ledger View; you can add new payees and "
"categories while entering a transaction or by going to the Payees or "
"Categories View before entering the transaction."
msgstr ""
"Če želite dodati druge transakcije, pojdite v pogled Glavne knjige; nove "
"prejemnike plačil in kategorije lahko dodate med vnosom transakcije ali "
"tako, da odprete pogled prejemnikov plačil ali kategorij, preden vnesete "
"transakcijo."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:378
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on which option you chose when setting up the data file, you will "
"probably find that the default Categories do not exactly match your needs; "
"you can easily delete ones you know you are never going to need and add "
"others that you do need. But when you are entering a transaction, you only "
"have to type a few letters of a category and &kmymoney; will offer you a "
"dropdown list of the matching categories from which to choose."
msgstr ""
"Odvisno od možnosti, ki ste jo izbrali pri nastavljanju podatkovne datoteke, "
"boste verjetno ugotovili, da privzete kategorije ne ustrezajo vašim "
"potrebam; enostavno lahko izbrišete tiste, za katere veste, da jih nikoli ne "
"boste potrebovali, in dodate druge, ki jih potrebujete. Toda ko vnašate "
"transakcijo, morate vnesti le nekaj črk kategorije in &kmymoney; vam bo "
"ponudil spustni seznam ujemajočih se kategorij, med katerimi lahko izbirate."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:387
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can add different accounts managed by different institutions; the "
"favorite ones (also called preferred) will show when you open &kmymoney; but "
"you can quickly switch to any of the others."
msgstr ""
"Dodate lahko različne račune, ki jih upravljajo različne institucije; "
"priljubljene (imenovane tudi prednostne) bodo prikazane, ko odprete "
"&kmymoney; vendar lahko hitro preklopite na katero koli drugo."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:393
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you make a payment, &kmymoney; will work out what the next check number "
"should be; delete this if you are not making a check payment or edit it if "
"the first check you enter is not check number 1. Alternatively, it is "
"possible to switch off auto-increment of check numbers."
msgstr ""
"Ko izvedete plačilo, &kmymoney; bo ugotovil, kakšna naj bo naslednja "
"kontrolna številka; izbrišite to, če ne plačujete s čekom, ali ga uredite, "
"če prvi ček, ki ga vnesete, ni številka čeka 1. Druga možnost je, da "
"izklopite samodejno povečevanje številk čekov."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:400
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Every so often you may get statements of your account from the institutions "
"you use. You can reconcile your &kmymoney; accounts against these statements "
"so that you know you have an accurate representation of the current state of "
"your finances."
msgstr ""
"Vsake toliko časa lahko dobite izpiske svojega računa od institucij, ki jih "
"uporabljate. Lahko uskladite svoj račun &kmymoney; glede na te izpiske, tako "
"da boste vedeli, da imate natančen prikaz trenutnega stanja vaših financ."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:406
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you go to the Reports View, you will find several default reports. To "
"customize these, open the one most similar to the sort you prefer and then "
"select 'New' (not 'Copy'.) You can then customize this to your needs and "
"mark it as a preferred report if you wish."
msgstr ""
"Če greste v Pogled poročil, boste našli več privzetih poročil. Če jih želite "
"prilagoditi, odprite tistega, ki je najbolj podoben zvrsti, ki jo želite, in "
"nato izberite »Novo« (ne »Kopiraj«.) To lahko nato prilagodite svojim "
"potrebam in po želji označite kot prednostno poročilo."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:413
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Though &kmymoney; is not intended for use in a business context, if you are "
"running a business on your own and so do not need payroll functions, you may "
"find that &kmymoney; is sufficiently customizable to meet your needs, "
"particularly as it comes with budgeting and forecasting features, and you "
"can export your customized reports via CSV into other applications."
msgstr ""
"Čeprav &kmymoney; ni namenjen za uporabo v poslovnem kontekstu; če vodite "
"podjetje sami in zato ne potrebujete funkcij za obračun plač, boste morda "
"ugotovili, da je &kmymoney; dovolj prilagodljiv, da ustreza vašim potrebam, "
"zlasti ker ima funkcije za načrtovanje proračuna in napovedovanje, svoja "
"prilagojena poročila pa lahko izvozite prek CSV v druge aplikacije."

#. Tag: title
#: makemostof.docbook:422
#, no-c-format
msgid "Plugins"
msgstr "Vtičniki"

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:423
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While a detailed knowledge of plugins is not necessary to use &kmymoney;, a "
"basic understanding is helpful, as the concept is mentioned in many places "
"throughout this handbook. When &kmymoney; was originally designed, all "
"features and functionality were implemented within the source code of the "
"program. As more features and functionality were added to the program, a "
"plugin system was designed, so additional functionality could be added in a "
"way that did not require modification of any of the core source code files. "
"When &kmymoney; starts, it looks in a specific directory for any plugins, "
"and it creates the appropriate menu and configuration entries for those it "
"finds."
msgstr ""
"Medtem ko podrobno poznavanje vtičnikov ni potrebno za uporabo &kmymoney;, "
"je osnovno razumevanje koristno, saj je koncept omenjen na številnih mestih "
"v tem priročniku. Ko je bil &kmymoney; prvotno zasnovan, so bile vse "
"zmožnosti in funkcionalnosti implementirane znotraj izvorne kode programa. "
"Ko je bilo programu dodanih več zmožnosti in funkcionalnosti, je bil "
"zasnovan sistem vtičnikov, tako da je bilo mogoče dodati dodatne "
"funkcionalnosti na način, ki ne zahteva spreminjanja katere koli datoteke "
"osnovne izvorne kode. Ko se &kmymoney; zažene, poišče morebitne vtičnike v "
"določenem imeniku in ustvari ustrezen meni menija in konfiguracijske vnose "
"za tiste, ki jih najde."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:435
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the first plugins were written, even though their source code was "
"included with the complete source code of &kmymoney;, not all &Linux; "
"distributions included them in the versions they compiled. For some time, "
"the handbook included instructions for checking this and for compiling them "
"yourself, if necessary. At this point, many of the basic features of "
"&kmymoney; have been implemented as plugins, and they are included by all "
"distributions, as well as the &Windows;, &macOS;, Appimage, and other "
"versions distributed on the <ulink url=\"https://www.kmymoney.org"
"\">&kmymoney; web site</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Ko so bili napisani prvi vtičniki, čeprav je bila njihova izvorna koda "
"vključena v celotno izvorno kodo &kmymoney;, jih niso vse distribucije "
"&Linux; vključile v različice, ki so jih sestavili. Nekaj ​​časa so bila v "
"priročniku tudi navodila, kako to preveriti in jih po potrebi sestaviti "
"sami. Na tej točki je veliko osnovnih funkcij &kmymoney; implementirani kot "
"vtičniki in so vključeni v vse distribucije, pa tudi v različicah &Windows;, "
"&macOS;, Appimage in drugih, ki se distribuirajo na <ulink url=\"https://www."
"kmymoney.org\">spletnem mestu &kmymoney;</ulink>."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:446
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See the section on <link linkend=\"details.settings.plugins\">Plugins</link> "
"in the chapter on <link linkend=\"details.settings\">Settings</link> for "
"more information on determining which plugins are installed and active, and "
"how to configure them."
msgstr ""
"Poglejte razdelek <link linkend=\"details.settings.plugins\">Vtičniki</link> "
"v poglavju o <link linkend=\"details.settings\">Nastavitvah</link> za več "
"informacij o določanju, kateri vtičniki so nameščeni in aktivni in kako jih "
"konfigurirati."

#. Tag: para
#: makemostof.docbook:452
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you wish to write your own plugin in order to implement a new feature, "
"such as importing or exporting data in a custom format, you should use one "
"of the existing importer or exporter plugins as an example. If you do so, "
"please write to the developers' mailing list &devlist;, in case someone has "
"already started a similar effort, and because your work may be of interest "
"to other users."
msgstr ""
"Če želite napisati svoj vtičnik za implementacijo nove funkcije, kot je uvoz "
"ali izvoz podatkov v formatu po meri, uporabite enega od obstoječih "
"vtičnikov za uvoz ali izvoz kot primer. Če to storite, pišite na poštni "
"seznam razvijalcev &devlist;, če je kdo že začel podobno prizadevanje in ker "
"bi vaše delo lahko zanimalo druge uporabnike."

